Custom fonts
============

Keep font-family names the same and utilise font-weight and font-style to style.

Using @font-face - https://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/using-font-face/

When using Google fonts, either:
- Use <link> tag (recommended)
- Download files and include using @font-face
See here for more info - https://stackoverflow.com/questions/12316501/including-google-web-fonts-link-or-import/12380004

Example:

@font-face {
  font-family: "Gotham";
  src: local("Gotham"), url({{ 'gotham-book.woff2' | asset_url }}) format("woff2"), url({{ 'gotham-book.woff' | asset_url }}) format("woff");
  font-weight: normal;
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap;
}

@font-face {
  font-family: "Gotham";
  src: local("Gotham-Medium"), url({{ 'GothamSSm-Medium_Web.woff2' | asset_url }}) format("woff2"), url({{ 'GothamSSm-Medium_Web.woff' | asset_url }}) format("woff");
  font-weight: 500;
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap;
}
